				                <div>Hello Jay,<br />
<br />
Thanks for the question.   A Redirect rule only uses  URL paths as criteria, excluding the query string. If you want to use the query string as part of the re-direct, you need to use a mod_rewrite.<br />
<br />
If you want to match some query string and redirect all URLs to some other URL, use a RewriteCond  together with a RewriteRule.    Try this out:<br />
<br />
RewriteEngine On<br />
RewriteCond %{QUERY_STRING} Itemid=571<br />
RewriteRule .* /contact-us [R=301]<br />
<br />
<br />
I hope this helps to resolve your problem!  Please let us know i you have any further questions or comments.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.</div>
