						<div style='float:right;margin:0px 0px 15px 15px;font-size:12px;color:#aaa'>2015-01-16 11:27 am</div>
				                <div>Hello Shnamuga,<br />
<br />
Sorry for the problem.  To make it so that you're forcing your domain name to leave out the trailing slash, you need to use .htaccess to rewrite the URL.  The .htaccess code would look like this:<br />
<br />
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d<br />
    RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} !^sub\. [NC]<br />
    RewriteRule ^(.+)/$ /$1 [L,R=301]<br />
<br />
I hope this helps to resolve the issue for you.  Please let us know if you have any further questions or comments.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.<br />
 </div>
