				                <div>Hello Jatinder,<br />
<br />
You may want to simply have the htaccess file ignore the directory with the second site. To ignore a directory, say a folder named 'abc' for example, use the following code at the top of the htaccess file.<br />
<br />
RewriteRule ^abc - [L,NC]<br />
<br />
This should allow it to ignore any rules thereafter for the 'abc' folder. You can then have a different .htaccess in the 'abc' folder so that directory has its own rules.<br />
<br />
Kindest Regards,<br />
Scott M</div>
