You will need to use regular expression pattern matching in order to make your redirect.  It will be something like:<br />
<br />
<i>RedirectMatch 301 /oldfolder/*.html /newfolder/*.html</i><br />
<br />
If you want to match the specific word "file", then you'd change the expression to include that word in the path like this:<br />
<br />
<i>RedirectMatch 301 /oldfolder/file*.html /newfolder/file*.html</i><br />
<br />
In this option,anything starting with the word "file" and ending in ".html" would be matched.  I hope this helps to answer your question, please let us know if you require any further  assistance.<br />
