				                <div>Hello Maheswaran,<br />
<br />
Thanks for the question, but we need a little more detail on what you're trying to do.  Are you trying to re-direct somewhere?  If so, where?  Are you re-directing to a single location based on any user-id? Based on the information you're providing, I'm guessing you're trying to do a re-direct to particular location based on getting a USER ID - bear in mind that this code does NOT determine a VALID user id.   You basically need to to do a RE-WRITE using regular expression to identify the pattern you're using for a condition. You're indicating that the UID could be any integer.  So, your rule might look like:<br />
<br />
RewriteRule  ^profilesmydomain.com/user/view/user/username/uid/([0-9]+)$   redirecttohere.com [NC,L]<br />
<br />
[NC,L] - "Flags", that tell Apache how to apply the rule. In this case, we're using two flags. "NC", tells Apache that this rule should be case-insensitive, and "L" tells Apache not to process any more rules if this one is used.  <br />
<br />
Coding support is beyond the scope of our support in the Support Center, but we do try to point you in the write direction.  Check out this <a href="https://www.addedbytes.com/articles/for-beginners/url-rewriting-for-beginners/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">article</a> to learn about URL re-writing.    This type of thing can be complicated,but the article provides a good base on how to create what you need.<br />
<br />
I hope this helps to answer your question, please let us know if you require any further  assistance.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.<br />
<br />
