				                <div>Hello Darren,<br />
<br />
No problem, the option you'll want to use is "Redirect an old domain to a new domain".<br />
<br />
<br />
You can put this code in the .htaccess file:<br />
<br />
RewriteEngine on<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^example.com [NC,OR]<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^www.example.com [NC]<br />
RewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://example.net/$1 [L,R=301,NC]<br />
<br />
You'll just want to replace example.com and example.net with the domains you want to redirect.</div>
