						<div style='float:right;margin:0px 0px 15px 15px;font-size:12px;color:#aaa'>2016-05-25 6:29 pm</div>
				                <div>Hello Tim,<br />
<br />
Part of what you said was true.  The part about the top to bottom reading of the .htaccess file is correct.  However, the condition issue about running the rule and then stopping is not exactly correct.  Your particular rewrite rule has the flag for NC (non-case sensitive) and L (last command - do not execute anything further).  So what's happening is that all your rewrites are going to the bottom and the last option is executed rewriting everything to venture4th.co (which I'm assuming is your main site).   You probably need to make your 301's into rewrites and then use a flag to end the re-write once it has been executed so that nothing else is processed. <br />
<br />
If you have any further questions or comments, please let us know.<br />
<br />
Regards,<br />
Arnel C.</div>
